    <note>Song(2) Xian [1565] He belonged to the lineage (zu) of Song(2) Qiqiu [3789], who was a chief councillor in the Southern Tang administration. His mother, Jiang(1) Shi, was the great granddaughter of a Hanlin academician, who served the Southern Tang, and the granddaughter and daughter of men who served Song. Affinal relation of Li(2) Gou [3513]. XCB, 174.13a, 189.5b, 6b, 192.1b; Li Gou, WJ, 30.13b; SHY:ZG, 65.22a; Songshi yi, 23.1b-2a; YLDD, 12428.14b. Jianyang XZ (1553), 2.22b, 9.8b. Jianning FZ, 15.27b. See also documentation for descendant, Ci [33118]. CBD, 1, 742.</note>
